data.title: Watch Seinfeld
data.meta_description: The "show about nothing" is a sitcom landmark, with comic Jerry and his three sardonic friends finding laughs in both the mundane and the ridiculous. Watch trailers & learn more.
data.text:
1. The Ex-Girlfriend

23m

After George breaks up with a woman he finds annoying, Jerry dates her and also finds her grating, yet he can’t bring himself to end the relationship.

2. The Pony Remark

23m

When Jerry’s parents visit New York, Jerry upsets a family member with a remark about ponies. Kramer wants to build "levels" in his apartment.

3. The Jacket

23m

Jerry buys an expensive suede jacket with an odd lining. Jerry and George get stuck alone with Elaine's intimidating father.

4. The Phone Message

23m

George goes to great lengths to prevent a woman he's dating from hearing an answering machine message. Jerry's date likes a commercial he hates.

5. The Apartment

23m

Jerry tells Elaine about an open apartment in his building, but soon regrets it. George wears a wedding ring to attract women.

6. The Statue

23m

Jerry is convinced that a house cleaner stole a statue from his apartment, threatening Elaine's deal with a client.

7. The Revenge

23m

George seeks revenge on his boss after he quits and then tries to get his job back. Jerry and Kramer think a laundromat owner stole money from Jerry.

8. The Heart Attack

23m

Jerry tries to decipher an unintelligible note he wrote in the middle of the night. George visits a holistic healer to deal with a medical issue.

9. The Deal

23m

Jerry and Elaine attempt to resume a sexual relationship — with strict rules. But Elaine's birthday might ruin the arrangement.

10. The Baby Shower

23m

Elaine hosts a friend's baby shower at Jerry's apartment, where George hopes to confront a former date. Kramer convinces Jerry to get illegal cable.

11. The Chinese Restaurant

23m

Jerry, Elaine and George wait — for what seems like forever — for a table at a Chinese restaurant, after being told it would be “five or 10 minutes.”

12. The Busboy

23m

Elaine and George fear they inadvertently got a busboy fired. Elaine realizes she can't stand a boyfriend who came from out of town to stay with her.

1. The Note

23m

Jerry scares a massage therapist, while George questions his sexuality after a massage. Kramer insists he saw Joe DiMaggio at a donut shop.

2. The Truth

23m

George breaks up with his girlfriend, who happens to be in the middle of helping Jerry with a tax audit. Kramer dates Elaine’s roommate.

3. The Pen

23m

Jerry and Elaine visit Florida for a ceremony honoring Jerry's dad. Jack Klompus gives Jerry a pen. Elaine hurts her back on an uncomfortable bed.

4. The Dog

23m

A drunk airplane passenger asks Jerry to look after his dog. George and Elaine find it awkward to hang out alone without Jerry.

5. The Library

23m

A stern library investigator goes after Jerry for an overdue book. George thinks a homeless man is a former teacher who tortured him in high school.

6. The Parking Garage

23m

The four lose their car in a parking garage, imperiling Elaine's new goldfish, George's night out with his parents and Jerry's painfully full bladder.

7. The Cafe

23m

Jerry befriends the owner of a Pakistani café and convinces him to make some changes. George's girlfriend asks him to take an IQ test.

8. The Tape

23m

Elaine anonymously records a racy voiceover for Jerry as a joke, causing George to become attracted to her. George orders baldness cream from China.

9. The Nose Job

23m

George's girlfriend gets plastic surgery. Jerry dates a woman he finds sexy but dislikes spending time with. Kramer wants a very specific jacket.

10. The Stranded

23m

George, Elaine and Jerry get stranded at a party on Long Island. The host later shows up unannounced at Jerry’s apartment.

11. The Alternate Side

23m

George gets a gig parking cars. Kramer lands a role in a Woody Allen movie. Jerry has an unpleasant rental car experience. Elaine dates a much older man.

12. The Red Dot

23m

George buys a cashmere sweater — with a small flaw — for Elaine. George has a sexual encounter at work. Elaine's boyfriend falls off the wagon.

13. The Subway

23m

During separate subway rides, Jerry befriends a nude man, George meets a woman, Kramer gets a horse-racing tip and Elaine tries to get to a wedding.

14. The Pez Dispenser

24m

A Pez dispenser causes George's girlfriend to flub a piano recital. Kramer creates a cologne that smells like the beach. Jerry hosts an intervention.

15. The Suicide

24m

Jerry gets close to a woman whose boyfriend tried to kill himself. George gets a mysterious warning from a psychic. Elaine fasts for a medical procedure.

16. The Fix-Up

24m

Jerry and Elaine fix George up with Elaine's friend, Cynthia, and soon after their first date, George learns that Cynthia may be pregnant.

17. The Boy Friend, Part I & II

47m

Jerry befriends baseball star Keith Hernandez, who takes an interest in Elaine. George concocts an unemployment scheme involving "Vandelay Industries."

18. The Limo

24m

Stranded at the airport, Jerry and George decide George should impersonate a man named "O’Brien" to get a ride in a limo back to the city.

19. The Good Samaritan

24m

Jerry dates a hit-and-run driver. George is offended by people who don’t say, "God bless you" after a sneeze. Mary Hart's voice causes issues for Kramer.

20. The Letter

24m

Jerry dates an artist who paints a portrait of Kramer. George feels obligated to buy art. Elaine wears a Baltimore cap to a Yankees game.

21. The Parking Space

24m

Kramer's friend, Mike, calls Jerry a "phony." George and Mike fight over a parallel parking spot. Jerry inadvertently breaks some bad news to a child.

22. The Keys

24m

Jerry asks for his spare keys back from Kramer, who then moves to California. George and Jerry discover Elaine wrote a script for "Murphy Brown."

1. The Trip, Part I

24m

George and Jerry go to LA for Jerry to appear on the “Tonight Show.” Kramer struggles to land acting roles. George annoys George Wendt and Corbin Bernsen.

2. The Trip, Part II

24m

After Kramer is detained in LA as a suspect in a string of murders, George and Jerry try to clear Kramer’s name and reunite with their friend.

3. The Pitch/Ticket

47m

Jerry and George develop a sitcom pitch for NBC, and George dates a network executive. Kramer is kicked in the head. Newman gets a speeding ticket.

4. The Wallet

24m

Morty claims a doctor stole his wallet. Elaine attempts to break up with her psychiatrist boyfriend. George negotiates the pilot deal with NBC.

5. The Watch

23m

Jerry tries to buy his old watch back from Uncle Leo. George makes a desperate plea to Russell Dalrymple. Kramer poses as Elaine’s boyfriend.

6. The Bubble Boy

23m

Jerry, George, Elaine and Susan visit a boy who lives in a plastic bubble. George and the boy argue over Trivial Pursuit. Jerry regrets an autograph.

7. The Cheever Letters

24m

Susan learns an uncomfortable truth about her father after telling him about the cabin. Jerry's dirty talk offends his date. Kramer seeks Cuban cigars.

8. The Opera

24m

George and Kramer try to sell extra tickets to "Pagliacci" on the street. Elaine and Jerry discover their separate connections to Joe Davola.

9. The Virgin

24m

Jerry’s new girlfriend is a virgin. Jerry pitches George's off-the-cuff "butler" storyline to NBC. Elaine causes Ping to have an accident.

10. The Contest

24m

George's mother catches him in a compromising position, leading the four to wager over who can be "master of their domain" for the longest.

11. The Airport

24m

Jerry takes a first-class seat on a flight, leaving Elaine to suffer in coach. George and Kramer rush from JFK to LaGuardia to pick them up.

12. The Pick

24m

Elaine mails out a revealing Christmas card. Jerry’s date thinks she sees him picking his nose. George visits a therapist. Kramer confronts Calvin Klein.

13. The Movie

23m

The gang agrees to meet for a movie. Jerry gets stuck in a taxi with a comic he doesn't like. George battles with a theater usher.

14. The Visa

24m

George dates a lawyer who's representing Ping in a lawsuit against Elaine. Babu gets detained by INS due to a mail mixup. Kramer punches Mickey Mantle.

15. The Shoes

23m

Elaine battles with a chef over a pair of shoes. Jerry and George visit an ill Russell and get caught leering at his daughter.

16. The Outing

22m

A student newspaper reporter mistakenly portrays George and Jerry as a couple, leading them to conflicted emotions about being perceived as gay.

17. The Old Man

22m

Elaine, Jerry and George volunteer with senior citizens. Kramer and Newman try to sell an older man's record collection. A woman's goiter shocks Elaine.

18. The Implant

23m

Elaine thinks Jerry’s girlfriend has breast implants. George tries to get a bereavement discount on airfare, and is accused of double-dipping a chip.

19. The Junior Mint

23m

Jerry can't remember his girlfriend's name, only that it rhymes with a female body part. Kramer and Jerry observe a surgery. George buys expensive art.

20. The Smelly Car

23m

An overwhelming odor takes hold in Jerry's car, and he can’t get it out. George learns that Susan is dating a woman, who becomes attracted to Kramer.

21. The Handicap Spot

22m

Kramer convinces George to make an unfortunate parking decision. Kramer dates a wheelchair user. The gang buys a TV for a couple that breaks up.

22. The Pilot, Part I & II

46m

George and Jerry finally produce their sitcom pilot. George is bothered by a spot on his lip. Elaine thinks Monk's only hires large-breasted servers.

1. The Mango

23m

George struggles to satisfy his new girlfriend. Elaine admits to "faking it" with Jerry in the past. Kramer gets banned from a fruit stand.

2. The Puffy Shirt

23m

Kramer dates a "low talker," leading to an embarrassing fashion moment for Jerry on TV. George gets noticed for his "exquisite" hands.

3. The Glasses

23m

George creates a fiasco involving a sugar-addicted optometrist, ladies' eyeglasses and Jerry's girlfriend. Elaine thinks a dog bite gives her rabies.

4. The Sniffing Accountant

23m

Jerry and Kramer think their accountant is on drugs. Elaine fights with her boyfriend about punctuation. George interviews to be a bra salesman.

5. The Bris

22m

Jerry and Elaine arrange an ill-fated circumcision ceremony. George's good parking spot at a hospital gets ruined. Kramer sees a "pig man."

6. The Lip Reader

23m

George gets caught on TV eating a messy sundae. Jerry dates a deaf tennis official. Kramer auditions to be a "ball man." Elaine fakes hearing loss.

7. The Non-Fat Yogurt

23m

The gang gets suspicious of a supposed “non-fat” frozen yogurt shop. Elaine dates George's nemesis, Lloyd Braun. Jerry curses in front of a kid.

8. The Barber

23m

George starts a new job he knows nothing about and may never have even been offered. Jerry tries to switch barbers. Elaine hosts a bachelor auction.

9. The Masseuse

23m

Elaine dates a man who shares his name with a serial killer. George becomes oddly drawn to Jerry’s masseuse girlfriend, who refuses to massage Jerry.

10. The Cigar Store Indian

23m

Jerry gives Elaine an offensive gift. Frank gets mad at Elaine over a "TV Guide." Kramer pitches a book about coffee tables. George gets grounded.

11. The Conversion

23m

George wants to convert to Latvian Orthodox. A sister at the church finds Kramer irresistible. Jerry discovers fungicide in his girlfriend’s apartment.

12. The Stall

23m

A woman withholds toilet paper from Elaine. George becomes enamored with Elaine's "cool guy" boyfriend. Kramer keeps calling a phone sex line.

13. The Dinner Party

23m

George and Kramer (and George's jacket) cause havoc at a wine shop. A babka and a black-and-white cookie spell trouble for Jerry and Elaine at a bakery.

14. The Marine Biologist

23m

Jerry tells George's ex-crush that George is now a marine biologist. Elaine has a run-in with a Russian author. Kramer hits golf balls into the ocean.

15. The Pie

23m

Jerry’s girlfriend’s father, Poppie, is "a little sloppy." Kramer notices a mannequin looks just like Elaine. George buys a suit that "swooshes."

16. The Stand-In

23m

Kramer gives questionable advice to his friend, Mickey. Jerry tries to cheer up his hospitalized friend. Elaine dates a man who "took it out."

17. The Wife

23m

Jerry's girlfriend poses as his wife for a dry cleaning discount. Elaine gets mixed signals from a guy at the gym. George pees in the shower.

18. The Raincoats, Part I & II

43m

Elaine dates a "close talker." George sells Frank’s old clothes. Kramer and Morty try to sell raincoats. Jerry and his girlfriend see "Schindler's List."

19. The Fire

22m

George struggles to keep his cool in a fire. Elaine's co-worker heckles Jerry’s act, and Jerry's retaliation causes an accident.

20. The Hamptons

23m

The gang visits a friend's new baby in the Hamptons. George's girlfriend goes topless. A doctor's wording puzzles Elaine. George experiences "shrinkage."

21. The Opposite

23m

George does the opposite of everything his instincts say. Jerry is "Even Steven." Kramer promotes his coffee table book. Elaine falls on hard times.

1. The Chaperone

23m

Jerry dates a Miss America contestant — with Kramer as a self-appointed chaperone. George proposes new Yankees uniforms. Elaine gets a new job.

2. The Big Salad

23m

George seeks credit for buying a salad. Elaine searches for a rare pencil. Jerry dates a woman who dated Newman. Kramer's golf game leads to trouble.

3. The Pledge Drive

23m

Jerry volunteers for a PBS pledge drive. A "high talker" confounds Elaine. Jerry cashes old checks from his Nana. Mr. Pitt eats a candy bar strangely.

4. The Chinese Woman

23m

Jerry dates a woman with a confusing last name who offers advice to Estelle. Kramer switches to boxer shorts. Frank's lawyer wears a cape.

5. The Couch

23m

George cuts corners on a book club assignment. Kramer and Poppie start a pizza business. Jerry’s couch gets defiled. Elaine's personal views are tested.

6. The Gymnast

23m

Jerry dates a gymnast. Mr. Pitt becomes obsessed with a 3D image. George eats "trash" and reveals an odd bathroom habit. Kramer gets a kidney stone.

7. The Soup

23m

Jerry bickers with Bania over what constitutes a "meal." Elaine's English visitor overstays his welcome. George has an awkward date with a waitress.

8. The Mom & Pop Store

23m

Kramer takes all of Jerry’s shoes to get cleaned. George brags about buying Jon Voight’s car. The gang goes to Tim Whatley’s Thanksgiving party.

9. The Secretary

23m

George gets too close to his new assistant. Jerry uses unethical dry cleaners. Elaine and Kramer have an adventure at Barneys.

10. The Race

24m

An old rival accuses Jerry of cheating in a race years ago. Elaine dates a communist and gets banned by a restaurant. Kramer becomes a mall Santa.

11. The Switch

23m

Jerry wants to break up with a woman to date her roommate. George thinks his girlfriend has an eating disorder. Kramer’s first name is revealed.

12. The Label Maker

23m

Whatley "regifts" a label maker to thank Jerry for Super Bowl tickets. Kramer and Newman play Risk. George's girlfriend's roommate looks just like him.

13. The Scofflaw

23m

A friend lies to Jerry and George about having cancer. Elaine tries to get back at an ex-boyfriend. Kramer helps track down a parking “scofflaw.”

14. 100th Episode Special

45m

This highlight show looks back at the funniest moments from the first 99 episodes of the series.

15. The Beard

24m

Elaine falls for a gay man. Jerry tries to prove that he doesn't watch "Melrose Place." George dates a bald woman. Kramer gets paid to be in police lineups.

16. The Kiss Hello

23m

George is angered by a cancellation policy. Kramer's idea to make their building more friendly irks Jerry. Morty and Uncle Leo fight over $50.

17. The Doorman

23m

Jerry and Elaine have run-ins with the doorman at Mr. Pitt's building. Frank and Kramer develop a new undergarment for men.

18. The Jimmy

24m

A mutual acquaintance refers to himself strangely. Jerry get suspicious of Whatley. George eats spicy food. Kramer’s dental visit leads to a mix-up.

19. The Doodle

23m

Jerry gets fleas in his apartment. George drapes himself in velvet. Kramer craves specific peaches. Jerry's family indulges themselves at the Plaza Hotel.

20. The Fusilli Jerry

23m

Kramer crafts a pasta statue of Jerry. Puddy uses Jerry’s "move" on Elaine. Kramer is issued the wrong vanity license plate. Estelle gets plastic surgery.

21. The Diplomats Club

23m

Mr. Pitt thinks Elaine's trying to kill him. Jerry's act gets sidetracked by an airline pilot. Kramer wagers with a Texan at the airport.

22. The Face Painter

23m

Puddy’s hockey fandom unnerves Elaine and an unsuspecting priest. George tries to tell his girlfriend he loves her. Kramer feuds with a chimpanzee.

23. The Understudy

24m

George runs over Bette Midler in a softball game. Jerry’s girlfriend cries easily. Elaine thinks her manicurists are making fun of her.

1. The Engagement

24m

George and Jerry lament their lack of direction in life, leading George to propose to ex-girlfriend Susan. Elaine turns to Newman to help kidnap a dog.

2. The Postponement

23m

George gets stressed out about his engagement. Elaine's rabbi has loose lips. Kramer spills hot coffee on himself at a movie with Jerry.

3. The Maestro

23m

Elaine's boyfriend insists on being called "Maestro." George gets a chair for a security guard. Kramer hires a lawyer. Jerry looks for houses in Tuscany.

4. The Wink

23m

A grapefruit causes problems for George. Jerry hides his disdain for meat. Elaine dates a wake-up service caller. Kramer needs a favor from Paul O'Neill.

5. The Hot Tub

23m

Jerry helps marathon runner Jean-Paul, who overslept for his last big race. George does business with Texans who swear a lot. Kramer gets a hot tub.

6. The Soup Nazi

23m

A soup stand owner's strict ordering rules cause chaos for the gang. Jerry and his girlfriend call each other “Schmoopie.” Elaine’s armoire get stolen.

7. The Secret Code

23m

George refuses to reveal his ATM code. Jerry’s foot keeps falling asleep. Elaine dates a man who doesn’t remember meeting her. Kramer assists the FDNY.

8. The Pool Guy

23m

Jerry’s pool guy tries to befriend him. Elaine starts hanging out with Susan, enraging George. Kramer's phone number gets confused with Moviefone.

9. The Sponge

23m

Elaine's favorite contraceptive is going off the market. Kramer joins an AIDS walk, but won't wear a ribbon. George tells Susan a secret about Jerry.

10. The Gum

23m

Kramer works with Lloyd Braun to renovate a movie theater. Jerry spends too much money on Chinese gum. An old friend thinks George has a mental illness.

11. The Rye

23m

Frank and Estelle meet Susan's parents for the first time. Kramer feeds a horse the wrong food. Jerry shops for a marble rye. Elaine dates a saxophonist.

12. The Caddy

23m

Steinbrenner thinks George is dead. Elaine's friend, Sue Ellen Mischke, distracts Jerry, leading to a lawsuit. Kramer seeks advice from a golf caddy.

13. The Seven

23m

George wants to name a child "Seven." Elaine and Kramer enlist Newman's help to settle a dispute. Jerry dates a woman who always wears the same dress.

14. The Cadillac, Part I & II

44m

Jerry buys his parents a Cadillac, causing trouble in their retirement community. Kramer fights with a cable guy. George wants to date Marisa Tomei.

15. The Shower Head

23m

Jerry and George push their parents to move to Florida. Jerry’s building gets annoying, new low-flow showerheads. Elaine tests positive for opium.

16. The Doll

23m

George finds one of Susan's dolls disturbing. Elaine wants to reconcile with the Maestro. Jerry meets Sally Weaver. Frank builds a billiards room.

17. The Friars Club

23m

Jerry loses a Friars Club jacket. George wants Jerry to date Susan’s best friend. Elaine suspects a co-worker. Kramer sleeps 20 minutes at a time.

18. The Wig Master

23m

George and Kramer have issues with a sketchy parking lot. Jerry returns a jacket out of spite. A wig master stays with George and Susan.

19. The Calzone

23m

Steinbrenner asks George to bring him a calzone every day. Elaine dates a man who never asked her out. Kramer warms up his clothes in an oven.

20. The Bottle Deposit, Part I & II

42m

Kramer and Newman hatch a bottle deposit scheme. Elaine buys famous golf clubs. A mechanic steals Jerry’s car. George is befuddled by a work assignment.

21. The Wait Out

23m

Jerry and Elaine date two people who broke up over a comment by George. Kramer wears jeans that are too tight. Mickey auditions for the Actors Studio.

22. The Invitations

24m

George takes a final shot at ending his engagement. Jerry falls in love with someone just like him. Kramer fights with a bank over the word "hello."

1. The Foundation

23m

George is asked to run a foundation in Susan's memory. Elaine takes charge of the Peterman catalog. Jerry comes to a realization about his engagement.

2. The Soulmate

23m

George spies on a foundation board meeting with his briefcase. Kramer falls for Jerry’s girlfriend. Elaine dates a man who doesn’t want children.

3. The Bizarro Jerry

24m

Elaine hangs out with “bizarro” versions of Jerry, George and Kramer. Kramer pretends to have a job. Jerry’s girlfriend has “man hands.”

4. The Little Kicks

23m

Elaine displays her embarrassing dancing skills. Jerry gets involved in bootleg filmmaking. George acts like a “bad boy” to woo Elaine’s employee.

5. The Package

23m

Kramer hatches a plan to get Jerry a refund on a stereo. Doctors won’t let Elaine see her medical chart. A photo store employee flirts with George.

6. The Fatigues

23m

Jerry becomes Bania’s mentor. Elaine struggles with an intimidating employee. Kramer hosts a Jewish singles night. George is bothered by an audiobook.

7. The Checks

23m

Jerry gets checks for 12 cents. Kramer hosts Japanese businessmen. Elaine's boyfriend thinks Jerry is poor. George encounters a carpet cleaning cult.

8. The Chicken Roaster

23m

A Kenny Rogers Roasters restaurant opens in the area. Elaine gets audited by Peterman for excessive spending. George tries to retrieve a Russian hat.

9. The Abstinence

23m

Abstaining from sex has opposite effects on Elaine and George. Jerry gets bumped from career day at his high school. Kramer opens a smoking lounge.

10. The Andrea Doria

23m

George competes for an apartment with a shipwreck survivor. Kramer seeks medical care from a veterinarian. Jerry helps Newman get a transfer to Hawaii.

11. The Little Jerry

23m

George dates a prison inmate. A bodega owner displays Jerry’s bounced check. Kramer buys a rooster. Elaine wants her boyfriend to grow his hair out.

16. The Pothole

23m

George loses his keys in a pothole. Jerry drops his girlfriend's toothbrush in a toilet. Elaine gets food delivered to a closet. Kramer adopts a highway.

17. The English Patient

23m

Elaine hates “The English Patient.” A beautiful woman mistakes George for her boyfriend. An older man challenges Jerry to a weightlifting contest.

18. The Nap

23m

Jerry gets a kitchen remodel. George takes naps under his desk. Kramer swims in the East River. Elaine has a misunderstanding about a mattress.

19. The Yada Yada

27m

Tim Whatley converts to Judaism. Kramer and Mickey double date. George's girlfriend says, "yada yada" a lot. Jerry's accused of being an "anti-dentite."

20. The Millennium

23m

George tries to get fired. Elaine gets bad customer service. Kramer and Newman plan competing parties. Jerry's girlfriend moves him down her speed dial.

21. The Muffin Tops

23m

George pretends to be a tourist from Arkansas. Kramer starts a "Peterman Reality Tour." Elaine helps Lippman with his muffin shop. Jerry shaves his chest.

22. The Summer of George

23m

During a summer out of work, George acts as Jerry's dating intern. Elaine’s co-worker won't swing her arms. Kramer's a seat filler at the Tony Awards.

1. The Butter Shave

23m

George's co-workers think he has a physical disability. Kramer butters his body. Elaine and Puddy break up on a flight. Bania rides Jerry's coattails.

2. The Voice

23m

Jerry gives his girlfriend's stomach a funny voice. Kramer hires an intern. Elaine reunites with Puddy. George refuses to leave his job.

3. The Serenity Now

23m

Frank employs a new anger management strategy. George and Lloyd Braun sell computers. Elaine attends a bar mitzvah. Jerry expresses his feelings.

4. The Blood

23m

Jerry trains with Izzy Mandelbaum. Elaine becomes a babysitter. George adds food to his sex life. Kramer stores blood at his apartment.

5. The Junk Mail

23m

Kramer asks to stop getting mail. Elaine unwittingly falls for a TV pitchman. An old friend gives Jerry a van. George's parents want to see him less.

6. The Merv Griffin Show

23m

Kramer starts a talk show in his apartment. George must care for a squirrel. Jerry dates a woman for her toy collection. Elaine works with a "sidler."

7. The Slicer

24m

George tries to edit an incriminating photo in his boss’ office. Kramer buys a meat slicer. An alarm keeps Elaine awake. Jerry dates a dermatologist.

8. The Betrayal

24m

Elaine, George and Jerry go to India for Sue Ellen Mischke's wedding. Kramer’s friend, FDR, makes an ominous birthday wish.

9. The Apology

23m

Jerry's girlfriend is naked all day. George clashes with a friend who's in recovery. Kramer changes his shower habits. Elaine's co-worker hates germs.

10. The Strike

23m

Frank brings back his holiday, "Festivus." George invents a charity. Kramer's 12-year strike at a bagel shop ends. Elaine pursues a free sandwich.

11. The Dealership

23m

Jerry negotiates buying a car from Puddy. George can't get a Twix out of a vending machine. Kramer takes a salesman on a thrilling test drive.

12. The Reverse Peephole

23m

Jerry gets a bag that looks like a purse. Puddy wears a fur coat. George's wallet is stuffed too full. Newman has an affair with the super's wife.

13. The Cartoon

23m

Sally Weaver's one-woman show about Jerry is a hit. George's girlfriend resembles Jerry. A "New Yorker" cartoon confuses Elaine. Kramer stops talking.

14. The Strongbox

23m

George dates two women at once. Elaine dates a poor man. Jerry fails to recognize a man who lives next door. Kramer buys a strongbox for his valuables.

15. The Wizard

23m

Kramer "retires" in Florida. Jerry buys Morty a gadget. George lies about a house in the Hamptons. Elaine wonders if her boyfriend is Black.

16. The Burning

23m

Kramer and Mickey act out medical scenes. Puddy tells Elaine he's religious. Jerry’s girlfriend says, "It's me." George tries to "go out on a high note."

17. The Bookstore

23m

George takes a book into a store's bathroom. Kramer and Newman start a rickshaw service. Uncle Leo shoplifts. Elaine drunkenly makes out with a co-worker.

18. The Frogger

22m

George wants to preserve his high score on "Frogger." Elaine eats a vintage cake. Jerry's fear of a killer prevents him from ending a relationship.

19. The Maid

23m

Jerry starts sleeping with his maid. George's boss gives him an unwanted nickname. Elaine hates her new "646" phone number. Kramer gets lost downtown.

20. The Puerto Rican Day

23m

The gang gets stuck in traffic due to the Puerto Rican Day Parade. George has a laser pointed at him. George, Jerry and Kramer crash an open house.

21. The Clip Show, Part I & II

44m

Look back at the funniest clips, most memorable quotes and unseen footage in this retrospective of the landmark series' entire run.

22. Finale, Part I & II

56m

Jerry, George, Elaine and Kramer are arrested for violating a "good Samaritan" law, leading to a trial featuring characters from the show's past.
